1
00:00:00,155 --> 00:00:02,302
From now on, I’m going all out to win you over.

2
00:00:02,360 --> 00:00:03,976
Let’s go on a trip. I’ve booked everything.

3
00:00:04,262 --> 00:00:06,764
I want another fight with you.

4
00:00:06,942 --> 00:00:08,482
I haven’t been here for quite a while.

5
00:00:08,499 --> 00:00:10,715
Why did you just stand there and let him beat you like that, son?

6
00:00:10,991 --> 00:00:13,066
There's nothing to worry about with Yak's condition, right?

7
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:15,880
If there’s no harsh trigger, there should be no need to worry.

8
00:00:16,099 --> 00:00:18,322
Yak! Don’t let him beat you!

9
00:00:21,010 --> 00:00:24,602
Can I become a boxer under Phadetseuk boxing club?

10
00:00:24,730 --> 00:00:25,472
What?

11
00:00:35,477 --> 00:00:36,205
What is that, Yei?

12
00:00:37,758 --> 00:00:38,466
Nothing.

13
00:00:40,155 --> 00:00:40,868
Yei.

14
00:00:41,545 --> 00:00:42,207
Yei.

15
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:43,608
Hold on.

16
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:47,890
(Notice of Property Seizure)

17
00:00:48,348 --> 00:00:49,211
What’s going on, Yei?

18
00:00:50,042 --> 00:00:52,108
Is someone playing a prank on us?

19
00:00:52,703 --> 00:00:53,771
I'm not okay with this.

20
00:00:55,475 --> 00:00:56,303
It’s not a prank.

21
00:00:57,050 --> 00:00:57,783
Yei…

22
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,306
I took out a mortgage on our house

23
00:01:00,770 --> 00:01:01,980
because we were in the red during Covid.

24
00:01:03,342 --> 00:01:04,125
Yei, you moron.

25
00:01:04,629 --> 00:01:05,912
How could you do this?

26
00:01:06,351 --> 00:01:08,016
This is our mother’s house.

27
00:01:08,317 --> 00:01:09,982
Do you think everything is just a walk in the park?

28
00:01:12,022 --> 00:01:12,988
Yak, calm down.

29
00:01:13,208 --> 00:01:14,130
How could I calm down?

30
00:01:14,557 --> 00:01:16,173
This is a serious matter. How could he not tell me?

31
00:01:16,773 --> 00:01:17,512
Answer me, Yei.

32
00:01:18,059 --> 00:01:19,025
Why did you do this?

33
00:01:20,211 --> 00:01:21,456
Leave this matter to me.

34
00:01:22,297 --> 00:01:23,505
I’ll sort this out somehow.

35
00:01:24,229 --> 00:01:25,034
Don’t worry.

36
00:01:25,174 --> 00:01:26,819
Stop treating me like I’m a child.

37
00:01:27,349 --> 00:01:28,468
I’m your freaking brother.

38
00:01:28,940 --> 00:01:30,262
I’m trying here.

39
00:01:30,762 --> 00:01:31,717
I’m really trying.

40
00:01:32,287 --> 00:01:33,717
Do you think I haven’t done anything at all?

41
00:01:33,730 --> 00:01:34,930
And look what you’ve done!

42
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:37,020
Yak, calm down.

43
00:01:37,834 --> 00:01:38,465
Calm down.

44
00:01:46,253 --> 00:01:46,869
Yak.

45
00:01:47,442 --> 00:01:48,445
Yak, come back.

46
00:01:48,917 --> 00:01:50,357
Oyei loves you very much, you know?

47
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:57,002
Aren’t we on the same team, Yak?

48
00:02:25,838 --> 00:02:26,859
Coming.

49
00:02:31,657 --> 00:02:32,281
Yak.

50
00:02:35,574 --> 00:02:36,465
What happened?

51
00:02:39,017 --> 00:02:39,653
Doc,

52
00:02:44,260 --> 00:02:45,380
can you hug me?

53
00:04:28,106 --> 00:04:28,908
Cheer up.

54
00:04:32,117 --> 00:04:33,165
Here it is.

55
00:04:33,656 --> 00:04:35,165
Thank you, ma’am.

56
00:04:39,954 --> 00:04:41,367
Shall we start?

57
00:04:53,635 --> 00:04:54,811
Come on, eat something, Yak.

58
00:04:56,148 --> 00:04:59,142
This bowl has both carbs and protein.

59
00:04:59,773 --> 00:05:02,022
It helps increase serotonin levels in your body,

60
00:05:02,204 --> 00:05:03,746
making your brain relaxed

61
00:05:05,620 --> 00:05:07,491
and also helping you feel invigorated.

62
00:05:09,377 --> 00:05:10,192
Eat it.

63
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:15,195
After what happened to me,

64
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,508
do you think I’ve got an appetite for anything?

65
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:20,619
Why did Yei do that to me?

66
00:05:22,740 --> 00:05:23,680
My head is bursting.

67
00:05:29,254 --> 00:05:29,905
Yak.

68
00:05:30,685 --> 00:05:32,020
I know you’re under stress,

69
00:05:32,607 --> 00:05:34,662
but you haven’t had anything all day.

70
00:05:35,278 --> 00:05:37,711
I have to make you eat no matter what.

71
00:05:38,493 --> 00:05:40,026
Come on, I’ll feed you.

72
00:05:42,517 --> 00:05:43,315
Open your mouth.

73
00:05:43,546 --> 00:05:44,170
Ahhhh.

74
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:45,945
Ahhhh.

75
00:05:46,939 --> 00:05:47,604
There you go.

76
00:05:48,385 --> 00:05:49,031
Chew it.

77
00:05:52,922 --> 00:05:53,804
Let’s eat together.

78
00:05:57,977 --> 00:05:58,868
Here we go.

79
00:06:02,745 --> 00:06:03,441
Wow.

80
00:06:06,269 --> 00:06:07,508
It’s really yummy.

81
00:06:07,945 --> 00:06:09,200
It’s yummier than other days.

82
00:06:09,887 --> 00:06:10,620
Try it.

83
00:06:11,859 --> 00:06:12,475
Come on.

84
00:06:17,810 --> 00:06:18,509
It’s good, right?

85
00:06:41,244 --> 00:06:42,562
Your hug is really warm.

86
00:06:43,434 --> 00:06:44,137
You know that?

87
00:06:47,730 --> 00:06:49,714
Mrs. Monthakarn once said,

88
00:06:50,342 --> 00:06:51,921
"A hug is free,

89
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:53,826
a boost of energy.

90
00:06:54,917 --> 00:06:56,905
Hug as much as you wish, never hold back a bit."

91
00:06:59,392 --> 00:07:00,610
She has a motto for it?

92
00:07:03,195 --> 00:07:04,309
I love Mrs. Monthakarn so much.

93
00:07:04,829 --> 00:07:06,607
Hey, what about me?

94
00:07:10,026 --> 00:07:10,770
As for you,

95
00:07:11,577 --> 00:07:12,414
I love you the most,

96
00:07:13,277 --> 00:07:14,414
more than anyone.

97
00:07:24,288 --> 00:07:24,915
Yak.

98
00:07:25,228 --> 00:07:25,868
Hm?

99
00:07:26,631 --> 00:07:27,976
Do you know what you want to do about it yet?

100
00:07:32,364 --> 00:07:34,608
Actually, I have some savings.

101
00:07:35,632 --> 00:07:37,060
I’ll give them to Yei,

102
00:07:38,075 --> 00:07:39,465
though I don’t know if it’s enough.

103
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:42,851
I think you should go talk with the bank.

104
00:07:43,290 --> 00:07:45,056
Maybe you can ask for a payment deferral.

105
00:07:46,845 --> 00:07:47,505
Okay.

106
00:07:47,936 --> 00:07:51,407
But you should clear the air with Yei first and foremost.

107
00:07:53,358 --> 00:07:55,162
No, I don’t want to see his face.

108
00:07:57,394 --> 00:07:58,017
Hey,

109
00:07:58,617 --> 00:08:00,225
are you so mad that you want to throw some punches, or what?

110
00:08:00,374 --> 00:08:01,905
Why can’t you two sit down and talk it out?

111
00:08:05,108 --> 00:08:05,768
That’s right!

112
00:08:07,262 --> 00:08:08,103
Thanks, Doc.

113
00:08:09,386 --> 00:08:10,171
For what?

114
00:08:11,663 --> 00:08:12,220
Yak!

115
00:08:13,914 --> 00:08:16,416
Thanks for giving me an idea.

116
00:08:18,751 --> 00:08:19,414
Yak.

117
00:08:20,068 --> 00:08:20,712
Yak!

118
00:08:21,010 --> 00:08:21,675
Yak.

119
00:08:21,737 --> 00:08:22,573
Thanks, Doc.

120
00:08:22,626 --> 00:08:23,312
Yak.

121
00:08:36,032 --> 00:08:37,303
I want to fight with the higher-ranked.

122
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:41,700
I don’t think you’re ready for that.

123
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:47,056
But it’s the only way we can earn a lot of money fast.

124
00:08:48,290 --> 00:08:49,811
We don’t have much time left.

125
00:08:51,225 --> 00:08:53,005
Can you really stand seeing our mother’s house go?

126
00:08:58,764 --> 00:08:59,463
Still no.

127
00:09:05,868 --> 00:09:06,534
How about this?

128
00:09:07,231 --> 00:09:08,962
Take my savings and buy us some time.

129
00:09:10,613 --> 00:09:11,768
Keep your money.

130
00:09:12,056 --> 00:09:13,010
Leave this matter to me.

131
00:09:13,355 --> 00:09:14,671
What the hell is wrong with you, Yei?

132
00:09:14,961 --> 00:09:16,222
What do you want to do?

133
00:09:16,362 --> 00:09:17,712
You don't agree with any of the ideas I offer.

134
00:09:18,020 --> 00:09:19,712
It’s clear you can’t manage this.

135
00:09:20,905 --> 00:09:21,727
Stay out of this.

136
00:09:22,235 --> 00:09:23,506
I’ll find a way myself.

137
00:09:23,540 --> 00:09:24,604
This is a way.

138
00:09:25,031 --> 00:09:26,514
I’m giving you a way out here.

139
00:09:27,045 --> 00:09:28,474
Have you ever listened to me?

140
00:09:28,983 --> 00:09:29,977
Seriously,

141
00:09:30,979 --> 00:09:32,416
do you still see me as your brother?

142
00:09:47,465 --> 00:09:49,200
They're still clashing.

143
00:09:49,626 --> 00:09:50,851
No idea when they'll make peace.

144
00:09:52,014 --> 00:09:53,168
(Don’t worry too much, Cher.)

145
00:09:53,844 --> 00:09:55,220
(You used to say, right?)

146
00:09:55,659 --> 00:09:57,505
They are very loving brothers.

147
00:09:57,991 --> 00:09:59,749
If their love is strong enough,

148
00:10:00,706 --> 00:10:02,309
they can definitely get through this problem.

149
00:10:02,948 --> 00:10:04,878
Call me if there’s an update.

150
00:10:05,394 --> 00:10:06,536
(Okay, I will.)

151
00:10:43,034 --> 00:10:43,711
Feel better?

152
00:10:46,429 --> 00:10:47,808
You have such good, strong hands.

153
00:10:50,607 --> 00:10:51,205
Yak.

154
00:10:53,214 --> 00:10:54,170
Can I ask you something?

155
00:10:55,349 --> 00:10:55,909
Yes.

156
00:10:57,037 --> 00:10:58,305
Are you really going to compete in a bout?

157
00:10:58,920 --> 00:10:59,554
Yes.

158
00:11:00,527 --> 00:11:02,860
It’s the only way to help Yei

159
00:11:03,620 --> 00:11:06,512
and also save my mother’s house.

160
00:11:13,524 --> 00:11:14,506
Can I ask you this?

161
00:11:15,642 --> 00:11:17,352
Why do you want to be a boxer?

162
00:11:22,109 --> 00:11:24,810
When I was a baby,

163
00:11:26,011 --> 00:11:27,557
I was really small when I was born.

164
00:11:28,684 --> 00:11:30,817
So Mom and Dad named me Yoryak.

165
00:11:31,561 --> 00:11:36,567
They wanted me to be tough and strong like giants.

166
00:11:37,324 --> 00:11:37,982
And also,

167
00:11:39,094 --> 00:11:40,617
when Oyei boxed in his world champion fight,

168
00:11:41,551 --> 00:11:45,303
his movements in the ring were truly unforgettable.

169
00:11:46,231 --> 00:11:47,721
He was smaller than his opponent

170
00:11:48,339 --> 00:11:49,610
but he managed to take the world champion title from him.

171
00:11:51,072 --> 00:11:52,588
So I wanted to become a boxer like him.

172
00:11:56,454 --> 00:11:57,465
Do you find it weird

173
00:11:58,364 --> 00:12:00,771
that I have my own big brother as my idol?

174
00:12:05,028 --> 00:12:06,186
Not at all.

175
00:12:08,530 --> 00:12:10,410
I believe you can do it, definitely.

176
00:12:13,441 --> 00:12:14,109
Seriously?

177
00:12:15,884 --> 00:12:19,053
I don't even believe that I would be where I am.

178
00:12:20,564 --> 00:12:21,472
Do you really believe in me?

179
00:12:24,407 --> 00:12:26,160
You may think it’s hard to achieve now,

180
00:12:27,004 --> 00:12:28,582
but I’m sure you can get through it somehow.

181
00:12:37,517 --> 00:12:39,509
You’ll always have me by your side, you know.

182
00:13:04,137 --> 00:13:04,908
Yes, okay.

183
00:13:05,288 --> 00:13:05,908
Goodbye.

184
00:13:09,795 --> 00:13:11,188
What did they say, Yei?

185
00:13:12,659 --> 00:13:14,573
Andre, the world No. 2, had his match canceled

186
00:13:15,137 --> 00:13:16,573
but all the preparations were made,

187
00:13:17,220 --> 00:13:18,786
he's now looking for a new opponent to replace the one who withdrew.

188
00:13:22,029 --> 00:13:24,368
Zazaki, do you want to do this?

189
00:13:26,053 --> 00:13:26,918
What about Yoryak-san?

190
00:13:27,226 --> 00:13:28,511
Yak isn’t ready.

191
00:13:28,989 --> 00:13:30,014
His shoulder hasn’t healed yet.

192
00:13:30,034 --> 00:13:30,434
I think…

193
00:13:30,445 --> 00:13:31,268
I’m taking on this fight.

194
00:13:31,558 --> 00:13:33,106
But I called and checked with the hospital.

195
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:35,106
Your shoulder is still a problem.

196
00:13:35,140 --> 00:13:36,914
I’m okay. I want to fight.

197
00:13:37,109 --> 00:13:38,604
Call them and arrange this match.

198
00:13:38,650 --> 00:13:41,108
Zazaki has received many challenges,

199
00:13:41,448 --> 00:13:42,115
right, Cher?

200
00:13:42,330 --> 00:13:45,677
Yes, we’ve received many.

201
00:13:45,724 --> 00:13:49,706
But here, the person who decides who competes in which bout is me.

202
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:02,714
Hello, Aunt Nipa.

203
00:14:05,540 --> 00:14:06,365
What happened to Dad?!

204
00:14:28,278 --> 00:14:28,847
Yei.

205
00:14:31,488 --> 00:14:32,325
I’m not going.

206
00:14:34,278 --> 00:14:35,222
Why not, Yei?

207
00:14:35,702 --> 00:14:36,813
Our dad is in the hospital.

208
00:14:38,179 --> 00:14:39,265
When he left us,

209
00:14:39,728 --> 00:14:41,220
he didn’t seem to care about us at all.

210
00:14:42,213 --> 00:14:43,408
Not long after Mom’s death,

211
00:14:43,877 --> 00:14:45,020
he came to me and said,

212
00:14:45,484 --> 00:14:47,616
“From now on, you’re in charge of this place,”

213
00:14:48,481 --> 00:14:49,804
and then he just left everything behind.

214
00:14:50,816 --> 00:14:53,613
Come on, Yei. He’s sick now.

215
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:56,167
He told his new wife to call us after he fell sick.

216
00:14:56,619 --> 00:14:57,982
If he loves that side so much,

217
00:14:58,853 --> 00:15:00,213
why would he bother with us?

218
00:15:00,622 --> 00:15:01,902
He has cancer, Yei.

219
00:15:03,937 --> 00:15:05,666
We don’t know how much time he has left.

220
00:15:06,871 --> 00:15:07,805
When Mom died,

221
00:15:09,434 --> 00:15:11,007
we weren’t there to say goodbye.

222
00:15:14,985 --> 00:15:16,512
I don’t want something like that to happen again.

223
00:15:27,102 --> 00:15:28,157
It’s not too uncomfortable, right?

224
00:15:28,174 --> 00:15:28,825
No.

225
00:15:31,382 --> 00:15:32,259
Hello, sir.

226
00:15:32,402 --> 00:15:33,262
Hello, Aunt Nipa.

227
00:15:33,552 --> 00:15:34,305
Hello.

228
00:15:38,002 --> 00:15:40,161
This is Dr. Wandee.

229
00:15:41,438 --> 00:15:42,194
Hello, sir.

230
00:15:42,210 --> 00:15:43,013
Hello.

231
00:15:43,188 --> 00:15:44,207
How are you feeling?

232
00:15:44,595 --> 00:15:47,220
I still feel a bit strange in my stomach.

233
00:15:49,151 --> 00:15:50,869
I talked to your doctor.

234
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:53,912
He said it’s not in a serious stage.

235
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,804
There’s a chance for you to fully heal.

236
00:15:56,237 --> 00:15:58,109
Really? That’s great news.

237
00:15:58,918 --> 00:16:00,152
Honey, you heard him, right?

238
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,050
Don’t give up easily, okay?

239
00:16:02,133 --> 00:16:02,715
Okay.

240
00:16:05,314 --> 00:16:08,976
Your doctor also said you could go home today.

241
00:16:14,232 --> 00:16:14,911
Doctor,

242
00:16:15,745 --> 00:16:18,773
I reckon I met you once at our boxing club, right?

243
00:16:19,577 --> 00:16:22,902
Yes, you have quite a good memory.

244
00:16:23,059 --> 00:16:25,016
I was there, sitting in a corner.

245
00:16:25,133 --> 00:16:26,779
I have the eye of a boxer.

246
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:31,185
However, how do you know my sons?

247
00:16:32,755 --> 00:16:33,512
Ah…

248
00:16:34,980 --> 00:16:38,731
Well, I’m...

249
00:16:42,470 --> 00:16:45,179
Dee is my boyfriend. He’s the one.

250
00:16:46,242 --> 00:16:47,268
Not yet.

251
00:16:47,804 --> 00:16:48,768
But almost.

252
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:53,614
Doctor,

253
00:16:54,642 --> 00:16:55,317
Cher.

254
00:16:56,718 --> 00:16:57,314
Yes?

255
00:16:57,662 --> 00:16:59,185
Are you two cursed or something?

256
00:16:59,394 --> 00:17:01,517
Why did you choose to be with my sons out of everyone?

257
00:17:06,748 --> 00:17:07,985
What a dry joke there, Dad.

258
00:17:09,402 --> 00:17:10,154
Yei.

259
00:17:13,930 --> 00:17:15,311
We’re in a good mood here.

260
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:16,610
What’s wrong with you?

261
00:17:17,071 --> 00:17:18,097
Why do you always rain on people’s parades?

262
00:17:19,051 --> 00:17:20,819
Yak, you want a piece of me?

263
00:17:21,251 --> 00:17:22,413
You keep getting under my skin.

264
00:17:22,420 --> 00:17:23,751
Who's getting under whose skin exactly?

265
00:17:24,484 --> 00:17:25,186
Isn’t that you?

266
00:17:26,308 --> 00:17:26,977
Yak.

267
00:17:27,157 --> 00:17:27,807
Yeah?

268
00:17:28,048 --> 00:17:29,463
Cut it out!

269
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:31,414
What’s wrong with you two?

270
00:17:31,914 --> 00:17:33,207
Always bickering like dogs.

271
00:17:41,128 --> 00:17:43,210
They are having a little conflict at the moment.

272
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:44,162
Cher!

273
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,410
(Nipa Farm Resort)

274
00:17:54,425 --> 00:17:55,010
Here.

275
00:17:55,832 --> 00:17:56,619
These are yours.

276
00:17:58,109 --> 00:17:59,077
Do you remember?

277
00:17:59,536 --> 00:18:00,712
Our family rules–

278
00:18:01,293 --> 00:18:03,859
we settle conflicts with punches.

279
00:18:04,668 --> 00:18:05,705
You must not dodge.

280
00:18:06,973 --> 00:18:07,979
Now begin.

281
00:18:12,657 --> 00:18:13,309
Go ahead, Yei.

282
00:18:15,444 --> 00:18:16,180
You go first.

283
00:18:16,712 --> 00:18:18,019
Aren’t you so eager to have a fight?

284
00:18:18,798 --> 00:18:19,777
I don’t want that.

285
00:18:20,591 --> 00:18:21,423
I only want to clear things up.

286
00:18:23,543 --> 00:18:24,911
Why did you mortgage Mom’s house?

287
00:18:25,285 --> 00:18:26,211
You got into gambling?

288
00:18:30,579 --> 00:18:31,611
Save your words.

289
00:18:32,256 --> 00:18:33,032
Just throw a punch already.

290
00:18:39,579 --> 00:18:41,308
I asked if it’s a gambling problem?

291
00:18:42,037 --> 00:18:43,354
I never gamble.

292
00:18:44,506 --> 00:18:47,980
Then how come you’re in debt?

293
00:18:48,445 --> 00:18:49,625
Honey, I think we should stop them.

294
00:18:49,666 --> 00:18:50,561
Please stop them.

295
00:18:51,247 --> 00:18:51,703
Huh?

296
00:18:55,090 --> 00:18:56,425
It was because of Covid.

297
00:18:56,625 --> 00:18:58,637
With the news about people getting Covid from a boxing gym,

298
00:18:59,014 --> 00:19:00,429
we were told to temporarily close down.

299
00:19:00,942 --> 00:19:01,979
Everything began to fall apart after that.

300
00:19:02,386 --> 00:19:04,746
We had bills to pay but no income.

301
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:13,010
Covid wasn't the only reason, right, Yei?

302
00:19:13,847 --> 00:19:14,512
Huh?

303
00:19:20,038 --> 00:19:21,440
I'm asking you. Answer me.

304
00:19:21,825 --> 00:19:23,908
You spent money to support my dreams, didn't you?

305
00:19:24,128 --> 00:19:25,026
Didn’t you?

306
00:19:26,254 --> 00:19:27,632
I asked if it was that!

307
00:19:31,594 --> 00:19:32,610
Was that it, Yei?

308
00:19:33,531 --> 00:19:35,195
You spent money to help make me achieve the champion title?

309
00:19:36,395 --> 00:19:36,965
Huh?

310
00:19:38,247 --> 00:19:39,308
This is a serious matter.

311
00:19:39,328 --> 00:19:41,091
Why didn't you tell me?

312
00:19:41,605 --> 00:19:43,091
Why did you keep it from me?

313
00:19:43,191 --> 00:19:44,554
I'm not a child anymore!

314
00:19:45,456 --> 00:19:46,111
Yak!

315
00:19:48,297 --> 00:19:50,408
I didn’t want you to worry about this matter.

316
00:19:52,071 --> 00:19:53,711
I want you to focus on being a champion

317
00:19:54,755 --> 00:19:55,924
and your studies.

318
00:19:58,204 --> 00:19:59,905
If supporting me was such a burden,

319
00:20:01,989 --> 00:20:03,567
you didn't have to go this far.

320
00:20:04,210 --> 00:20:06,155
But I gave my word to Mom.

321
00:20:11,979 --> 00:20:12,619
Mom!

322
00:20:13,835 --> 00:20:14,749
What’s up, Yak?

323
00:20:14,776 --> 00:20:15,702
What’s up, Oyei?

324
00:20:16,832 --> 00:20:18,117
I won today, Mom.

325
00:20:18,297 --> 00:20:20,408
I’m getting closer to being a champion.

326
00:20:20,690 --> 00:20:21,331
Am I great?

327
00:20:21,554 --> 00:20:22,394
You are, dear.

328
00:20:22,493 --> 00:20:24,435
My son is the best.

329
00:20:27,345 --> 00:20:27,925
Yak,

330
00:20:28,487 --> 00:20:32,315
