331
00:20:33,807 --> 00:20:34,517
Sure, Mom.

332
00:20:41,976 --> 00:20:44,155
Then, I’ll wait outside.

333
00:20:44,663 --> 00:20:45,607
Hold on, Yei.

334
00:20:46,062 --> 00:20:47,703
I have something to tell you.

335
00:20:48,231 --> 00:20:49,117
Sit down.

336
00:20:50,561 --> 00:20:51,238
Okay, Mom.

337
00:20:56,592 --> 00:20:58,834
The doctor told me today

338
00:20:59,456 --> 00:21:02,912
that my breast cancer surgery had a few side effects.

339
00:21:03,730 --> 00:21:04,902
The cancer wasn't completely removed.

340
00:21:05,462 --> 00:21:07,305
It has spread to the bones in my legs.

341
00:21:19,638 --> 00:21:20,228
Yei.

342
00:21:21,561 --> 00:21:23,626
Can I ask you to help support Yak’s dream for me?

343
00:21:58,386 --> 00:22:00,155
Let me help get our house back, Yei.

344
00:22:02,060 --> 00:22:03,149
Let me help you.

345
00:22:07,880 --> 00:22:09,508
You can take all my savings.

346
00:22:13,063 --> 00:22:13,785
Take it, Yei.

347
00:22:21,091 --> 00:22:27,737
If it’s too heavy, you can put it down.

348
00:22:31,927 --> 00:22:33,109
Let me help carry the weight off of you.

349
00:22:52,131 --> 00:22:52,968
I’m...

350
00:22:54,090 --> 00:22:55,205
I’m sorry, Yak.

351
00:23:06,293 --> 00:23:07,011
It’s okay.

352
00:23:08,899 --> 00:23:10,054
We’re brothers, right?

353
00:23:28,136 --> 00:23:31,120
Here you are.

354
00:23:31,143 --> 00:23:32,131
Help her.

355
00:23:36,860 --> 00:23:37,816
Let’s start.

356
00:23:41,023 --> 00:23:43,911
It’s good to have a meal together once in a while.

357
00:23:45,651 --> 00:23:47,358
Kids, go ahead. Eat up.

358
00:23:48,497 --> 00:23:49,974
They all look good.

359
00:23:52,111 --> 00:23:54,905
These are all Oyei and Yak’s favorites.

360
00:23:55,537 --> 00:23:56,616
How do you know, Aunt Nipa?

361
00:24:01,143 --> 00:24:03,201
When their mother, Wan, was alive,

362
00:24:03,294 --> 00:24:04,902
she always made these dishes.

363
00:24:06,106 --> 00:24:10,869
Chicken Green Curry and Omelet with Onion are Yak’s favorite dishes.

364
00:24:12,093 --> 00:24:15,577
Kai Palo is Oyei’s favorite.

365
00:24:15,611 --> 00:24:16,370
Here you are, son.

366
00:24:21,915 --> 00:24:23,013
Well, I’m sorry.

367
00:24:23,435 --> 00:24:25,611
I don’t know Mrs. Wan’s secret recipes,

368
00:24:25,625 --> 00:24:27,275
but I did my best.

369
00:24:28,197 --> 00:24:30,703
I hope they are to your liking.

370
00:24:31,426 --> 00:24:32,213
Please give them a try.

371
00:24:46,205 --> 00:24:47,016
It’s quite good.

372
00:24:48,219 --> 00:24:49,311
It’s delicious, Aunt Nipa.

373
00:24:54,397 --> 00:24:56,420
Yes, it’s indeed good.

374
00:24:56,708 --> 00:24:58,536
You could even open a restaurant.

375
00:24:59,287 --> 00:25:01,567
True. I give you five stars.

376
00:25:43,213 --> 00:25:44,724
What’s the rush?

377
00:25:46,524 --> 00:25:47,174
Yei.

378
00:25:48,518 --> 00:25:50,456
Aren’t you being too mean to Aunt Nipa?

379
00:25:51,197 --> 00:25:53,472
What did I do? I didn’t do anything.

380
00:25:54,260 --> 00:25:55,755
I just didn’t feel like eating it, so I didn’t eat it.

381
00:25:55,771 --> 00:25:56,342
That’s it.

382
00:25:56,374 --> 00:25:58,174
But she prepared the food especially for us.

383
00:25:58,760 --> 00:25:59,546
Come on, Yak.

384
00:26:00,005 --> 00:26:01,315
Just because she made your favorite food,

385
00:26:01,491 --> 00:26:02,522
you already have a soft spot for her?

386
00:26:02,648 --> 00:26:03,776
That’s not what this is about.

387
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:06,605
Take it easy, Phadetseuk brothers.

388
00:26:07,010 --> 00:26:08,108
You guys just reconciled.

389
00:26:09,170 --> 00:26:11,120
Let’s call it a night.

390
00:26:11,703 --> 00:26:12,511
Do you agree, Dr. Dee?

391
00:26:13,248 --> 00:26:16,514
Yes, it’s been a long day today.

392
00:26:17,167 --> 00:26:17,774
Let’s go, Yak.

393
00:26:18,168 --> 00:26:18,957
Let’s go to bed.

394
00:26:19,762 --> 00:26:20,604
You can talk this out again tomorrow.

395
00:26:23,084 --> 00:26:24,057
Fine, I’ll go to bed.

396
00:26:24,951 --> 00:26:28,254
We have to get up early tomorrow for Mom’s memorial day.

397
00:26:29,632 --> 00:26:33,303
But... I don’t think those folks remember.

398
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:40,300
Yei.

399
00:26:56,272 --> 00:26:57,906
Yei, it’s me.

400
00:27:19,250 --> 00:27:19,980
Our mom was pretty, right?

401
00:27:23,512 --> 00:27:25,512
I can’t help but think back to the old days.

402
00:27:28,623 --> 00:27:30,832
But we haven’t changed at all.

403
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:33,502
