It may not come out beautiful.

414
00:28:10,343 --> 00:28:11,315
Please don’t be mad at me.

415
00:28:12,991 --> 00:28:14,542
She won’t be mad, come on.

416
00:28:15,321 --> 00:28:19,813
She’s probably happy to see her sons’ sweethearts making these for her.

417
00:28:27,696 --> 00:28:29,312
Hey, Yei, Yak.

418
00:28:29,789 --> 00:28:30,416
You’re here?

419
00:28:34,691 --> 00:28:35,977
Your garland making isn’t so bad, Doc.

420
00:28:39,030 --> 00:28:39,976
Make way for me.

421
00:28:40,019 --> 00:28:42,560
Oyei, can you put these in the kitchen?

422
00:28:43,640 --> 00:28:44,402
Let’s go.

423
00:28:46,890 --> 00:28:49,007
Aunt Nipa, where do you want me to put these?

424
00:28:50,311 --> 00:28:52,709
Here. Thank you.

425
00:28:58,457 --> 00:29:00,331
Oyei, Yoryak,

426
00:29:01,216 --> 00:29:03,201
come help me clean up a room at the resort.

427
00:29:04,863 --> 00:29:05,494
Okay.

428
00:29:05,586 --> 00:29:06,158
Let’s go.

429
00:29:18,601 --> 00:29:20,567
I thought you had already forgotten Mom.

430
00:29:25,422 --> 00:29:27,614
I never forgot her, not even for a day.

431
00:29:35,805 --> 00:29:36,620
Then...

432
00:29:38,247 --> 00:29:40,758
why did you leave us after she passed away?

433
00:29:43,625 --> 00:29:47,047
When I first met Oyei and Yoryak’s father,

434
00:29:47,622 --> 00:29:50,158
I didn’t recognize he was a former world champion.

435
00:29:51,140 --> 00:29:52,057
He was always wasted,

436
00:29:52,990 --> 00:29:57,706
picking fights wherever he went, loud and drunk.

437
00:30:00,865 --> 00:30:01,903
I didn’t leave you.

438
00:30:03,728 --> 00:30:05,402
It was too hard for me to continue living there.

439
00:30:07,897 --> 00:30:10,248
Everywhere I looked, I saw your mother’s face.

440
00:30:11,354 --> 00:30:13,857
I was a total mess back then.

441
00:30:14,687 --> 00:30:16,564
If I continued running our boxing gym,

442
00:30:18,105 --> 00:30:19,700
you two would have suffered the consequences.

443
00:30:21,672 --> 00:30:23,808
So, I decided to give everything to Oyei.

444
00:30:25,035 --> 00:30:26,611
I traveled around aimlessly.

445
00:30:28,114 --> 00:30:30,402
I didn’t want to live, not even for a day.

446
00:30:35,859 --> 00:30:37,567
What did you do?

447
00:30:38,527 --> 00:30:39,616
You went back to help him?

448
00:30:41,445 --> 00:30:43,611
I didn’t understand myself either why I did that.

449
00:30:46,152 --> 00:30:49,705
Every decision has its binary choices.

450
00:30:56,770 --> 00:30:58,308
My grandmother taught me that.

451
00:31:06,445 --> 00:31:07,106
I’m...

452
00:31:07,500 --> 00:31:08,562
I’m sorry, Dad.

453
00:31:11,133 --> 00:31:12,708
I should be the one saying sorry to you.

454
00:31:13,801 --> 00:31:14,408
Oyei,

455
00:31:15,882 --> 00:31:19,813
you are a great head of our family, much better than me.

456
00:31:22,482 --> 00:31:25,613
If your mom were around, she would be proud of you too.

457
00:31:26,998 --> 00:31:27,979
Like me.

458
00:31:28,386 --> 00:31:29,859
I’m also proud of you.

459
00:31:42,379 --> 00:31:43,109
But it’s…

460
00:31:43,754 --> 00:31:45,654
It’s so damn hard, Dad.

461
00:31:47,900 --> 00:31:49,660
You’ve done such a great job, Yei.

462
00:31:50,682 --> 00:31:52,408
Look how well I’ve grown up.

463
00:31:58,131 --> 00:32:04,112
Just as rivers full of water fill the ocean,

464
00:32:04,334 --> 00:32:09,099
so too does what is given here benefit the dead.

465
00:32:26,345 --> 00:32:27,014
Take this.

466
00:32:32,693 --> 00:32:34,099
