00:39:33,912 --> 00:39:35,514
Come up here for a photo, kids.

554
00:39:37,063 --> 00:39:37,899
Come on.

555
00:39:39,161 --> 00:39:39,813
Thank you.

556
00:39:47,558 --> 00:39:50,708
You are my sons’ sweethearts, which means you are our family.

557
00:39:52,154 --> 00:39:55,733
Thank you so much for taking care of my sons so well.

558
00:39:58,148 --> 00:39:58,712
Alright.

559
00:39:59,595 --> 00:40:00,509
Here we go.

560
00:40:00,773 --> 00:40:02,650
One, two, three.

561
00:40:03,274 --> 00:40:04,560
Another one, please.

562
00:40:05,111 --> 00:40:07,137
One, two, three.

563
00:40:07,577 --> 00:40:08,711
Okay.

564
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:11,317
Let’s do a big heart.

565
00:40:11,771 --> 00:40:12,983
Big heart.

566
00:40:14,088 --> 00:40:16,422
One, two, three.

567
00:40:18,115 --> 00:40:19,214
Okay.

568
00:40:31,931 --> 00:40:33,010
Give it back.

569
00:40:34,238 --> 00:40:35,564
Give it back to me.

570
00:40:36,518 --> 00:40:37,882
Why do you want it, Dee?

571
00:40:38,059 --> 00:40:39,817
You don’t have any of your parents left.

572
00:40:40,050 --> 00:40:41,718
Yeah. You don’t need it.

573
00:40:47,545 --> 00:40:48,312
Here you are.

574
00:40:49,244 --> 00:40:50,014
What’s on your mind?

575
00:40:58,702 --> 00:40:59,506
You know something?

576
00:41:00,339 --> 00:41:04,703
I always wonder if my parents loved me at all.

577
00:41:06,685 --> 00:41:08,134
Doc, come on.

578
00:41:10,251 --> 00:41:12,202
I was so envious of you and Oyei back there.

579
00:41:14,170 --> 00:41:18,223
Finally, you realized how much your father loves you and your brother.

580
00:41:20,696 --> 00:41:22,765
His love is big enough to extend to me.

581
00:41:33,331 --> 00:41:34,262
When I was a kid,

582
00:41:36,405 --> 00:41:40,308
I remember my parents were always busy.

583
00:41:41,324 --> 00:41:42,620
They traveled all the time.

584
00:41:45,042 --> 00:41:49,213
I had only Mrs. Monthakarn with me at every event.

585
00:41:50,684 --> 00:41:53,106
It was ruined, Mrs. Monthakarn.

586
00:41:54,552 --> 00:41:55,614
Let me see.

587
00:41:57,656 --> 00:42:00,189
Even though it’s ruined, it still looks pretty.

588
00:42:00,810 --> 00:42:02,411
It’s beautiful even with flaws.

589
00:42:03,008 --> 00:42:05,007
Is there such a thing that looks pretty with flaws?

590
00:42:05,857 --> 00:42:06,697
Yes, there is.

591
00:42:06,914 --> 00:42:10,120
Things don’t always have to be perfect to be beautiful.

592
00:42:10,853 --> 00:42:12,358
Even when they're ruined, they can still look pretty.

593
00:42:14,531 --> 00:42:17,656
Why do they have to have a Parents' Day at this school?

594
00:42:19,321 --> 00:42:20,223
Yeah, I wonder too.

595
00:42:21,345 --> 00:42:22,725
But regardless of the day,

596
00:42:22,745 --> 00:42:25,823
you always have this Mrs. Monthakarn beside you.

597
00:42:27,524 --> 00:42:28,408
Thank you.

598
00:42:30,068 --> 00:42:32,441
Come here. Let’s have a power-charging hug.

599
00:42:35,811 --> 00:42:37,407
Whether it was Father’s Day

600
00:42:39,269 --> 00:42:40,505
or Mother’s Day,

601
00:42:42,374 --> 00:42:46,306
the one who was always there for me was Mrs. Monthakarn.

602
00:42:48,567 --> 00:42:52,321
I couldn’t even recall

603
00:42:53,777 --> 00:42:55,761
if my parents ever told me they loved me

604
00:42:58,685 --> 00:43:00,508
or what their hugs felt like.

605
00:43:33,614 --> 00:43:35,404
That’s what Dee is hung up on?

606
00:43:37,650 --> 00:43:38,308
Yes.

607
00:43:39,725 --> 00:43:44,669
I think we should find a way to unlock this doubt in his heart.

608
00:43:48,866 --> 00:43:49,971
You can open your eyes, dear.

609
00:43:55,983 --> 00:43:56,720
What is this, Grandma?

610
00:44:01,657 --> 00:44:03,908
"I want every day to be a good day."

611
00:44:18,657 --> 00:44:19,577
Look at him.

612
00:44:20,102 --> 00:44:21,546
Smile to your dad.

613
00:44:23,534 --> 00:44:25,506
Look, he opens his eyes.

614
00:44:25,592 --> 00:44:26,688
Isn’t he cute?

615
00:44:29,140 --> 00:44:30,751
Mom, hold the cam and film me too.

616
00:44:30,848 --> 00:44:31,712
Sure.

617
00:44:33,653 --> 00:44:34,702
Smile, dear.

618
00:44:35,082 --> 00:44:36,943
Smile to the camera.

619
00:44:36,970 --> 00:44:39,442
My son is so cute.

620
00:44:41,641 --> 00:44:42,605
He’s my son.

621
00:44:45,425 --> 00:44:46,416
(Smile.)

622
00:44:49,155 --> 00:44:51,465
(Have you decided on his name?)

623
00:44:52,888 --> 00:44:53,908
(Yes, we have.)

624
00:44:54,871 --> 00:44:56,053
(His name is Wandee.)

625
00:44:56,361 --> 00:44:58,328
(I want him to always have a good day in his life.)

626
00:45:02,888 --> 00:45:04,460
(Look at the camera, dear.)

627
00:45:04,773 --> 00:45:06,794
(My handsome son, look at the camera, please.)

628
00:45:07,530 --> 00:45:08,877
(That’s my boy.)

629
00:45:10,173 --> 00:45:11,512
(He seems to like being filmed.)

630
00:45:27,245 --> 00:45:28,210
Mrs. Monthakarn.

631
00:45:31,259 --> 00:45:35,454
You are our love, you know.

632
00:45:38,860 --> 00:45:39,906
Come here. Let’s have a power-charging hug.

633
00:45:53,493 --> 00:45:54,814
A hug is free,

634
00:45:55,447 --> 00:45:56,666
a boost of energy.

635
00:45:57,388 --> 00:45:59,317
Hug as much as you wish, never hold back a bit.

636
00:46:16,291 --> 00:46:19,734
Seriously, when did you add Mrs. Monthakarn to your contacts?

637
00:46:20,234 --> 00:46:22,026
Are you trying to get my secrets from her?

638
00:46:23,229 --> 00:46:24,801
I've seen through everything.

639
00:46:25,878 --> 00:46:27,303
Is there any secret left?

640
00:46:29,118 --> 00:46:29,825
You perv!

641
00:46:36,130 --> 00:46:37,431
Today is such a good day.

642
00:46:37,988 --> 00:46:38,708
You know that?

643
00:46:44,248 --> 00:46:44,874
Here.

644
00:46:48,888 --> 00:46:49,511
Doc.

645
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:55,582
Going forward, every day of yours will be a good day.

646
00:47:00,038 --> 00:47:00,765
I'm taking off.

647
00:47:01,487 --> 00:47:02,742
If we keep this up,

648
00:47:02,980 --> 00:47:04,090
we won't make it home.

649
00:47:16,448 --> 00:47:19,977
That’s why I like to treat all special days specially—

650
00:47:20,810 --> 00:47:26,515
birthdays, graduation days, any anniversaries.

651
00:47:39,859 --> 00:47:40,909
Those are the days

652
00:47:43,859 --> 00:47:47,474
we get to see the widest and happiest smiles on people’s faces.

653
00:47:56,899 --> 00:47:58,832
The happy smiles

654
00:48:00,034 --> 00:48:01,405
that leave you with no doubt

655
00:48:01,794 --> 00:48:03,820
whether those people are truly loved or not.

656
00:48:07,146 --> 00:48:11,795
 It’s good that I have you, it's good when I'm with you 

657
00:48:12,085 --> 00:48:19,133
 All I need is you, that’s already too good to be true 

658
00:48:27,048 --> 00:48:30,497
 Just having a good day with you 

659
00:48:30,820 --> 00:48:33,149
 It’s good to have you 

660
00:48:33,465 --> 00:48:39,043
 Just us having each other, that’s all I could ask for 

661
00:48:39,177 --> 00:48:43,805
 It’s good that I have you, it's good when I'm with you 

662
00:48:44,081 --> 00:48:50,521
 All I need is you, that’s already too good to be true 

663
00:48:54,912 --> 00:48:56,376
He wants to challenge me already?

664
00:48:56,527 --> 00:49:00,305
He probably knows your shoulder still hurts, so he wants to fight with you.

665
00:49:00,703 --> 00:49:01,814
Is it okay for me to take this fight?

666
00:49:01,924 --> 00:49:04,309
You might need to rest and do physio for three months.

667
00:49:04,480 --> 00:49:09,616
Do you still see that mysterious man now that an important fight is approaching?

668
00:49:10,035 --> 00:49:10,960
Help me, Doc.

669
00:49:11,397 --> 00:49:12,515
I must help you, of course.

670
00:49:13,205 --> 00:49:15,025
I’m on Yoryak Phadetseuk’s team, right?
